1 (c) Property of any state-supported educational institution;
2 (d) Vending stand locations and facilities operated by blind persons under the
3 auspices of the Division of Kentucky Business Enterprise, regardless of
4 whether the property is owned by the federal, state, or a local government;
5 (e) Property of any free public library;
6 (f) Property in Fayette County, Kentucky, administered by the Department of
7 Military Affairs, Bluegrass Station Division;
8 (g) All privately owned leasehold interests in residential property when the
9 residential property is owned in fee simple by a purely public charity as of
10 July 1, 2020:
11 1. When the real property includes a residential property unit that is:
12 a. Leased by the purely public charity for a period of at least one (1)
13 year to an individual person who is fifty-five (55) years of age or
14 older;
15 b. Maintained as the individual person's permanent residence under a
16 lease agreement that:
17 i. Prohibits the lessee from subleasing the unit; and
18 ii. Provides that the lessee's possessory interest in the unit is
19 terminable by the lessor upon the death of the lessee, the
20 physical or mental inability of the lessee to continue to reside
21 in the unit, or the lessee's relocation to a nursing home or
22 similar assisted living facility; and
23 c. Constructed on or before July 1, 2020, or constructed after July 1,
24 2020, on land that was privately owned in fee simple by the purely
25 public charity on or before July 1, 2020;
26 2. If the fee simple ownership is transferred by the purely public charity
27 after July 1, 2020, it shall be transferred to another purely public charity
